Installation

1) Install RabbitMQ.
Installing RabbitMQ on Ubuntu 16.04
To install it on a newer Ubuntu version is very straightforward:

apt-get install -y erlang
apt-get install rabbitmq-server

##Installing RabbitMQ on Mac

Homebrew is the most straightforward option:

brew install rabbitmq


2) Then enable and start the RabbitMQ service:

systemctl enable rabbitmq-server
systemctl start rabbitmq-server

3) Check the status to make sure everything is running smooth:

systemctl status rabbitmq-server


4) The RabbitMQ scripts are installed into /usr/local/sbin. You can add it to your .bash_profile or .profile.

vim ~/.bash_profile

5) Then add it to the bottom of the file:

export PATH=$PATH:/usr/local/sbin

6) Restart the terminal to make sure the changes are in effect.

7) Now you can start the RabbitMQ server using the following command:

rabbitmq-server

8) Create a virtual enviroment:
"python3 -m venv py3env"

9) Enable virtualenv:
". py3env/bin/activate"

10) Install requirements:
pip install -r requirements.txt

11) Install MySQL:
    sudo apt-get update
    sudo apt-get install mysql-server
    mysql_secure_installation

12) Create MySQL user:
mysql -r
mysql> CREATE USER 'lpkagami'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED BY '3085luc9973';
mysql> GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON * . * TO 'lpkagami'@'localhost';

13) Copy acpypeserver folder into py3env;

14) Type "cd acpypeserver";

15) Type 'python3 manage.py makemigrations";

16) Type 'python3 manage.py migrate";

17) Type 'python3 manage.py runserver";

18) Open "http://127.0.0.1:8000/" in a browser;

19) Open acpypeserver in other terminal and enable the virtual enviroment;

20) Start Celery:
celery -A acpypeserver worker -l info


